--- SCENARIO: open draft posts pools publicly; status holds the metadata ---
# Players register from the group without opening a private chat, so the bot cannot DM them: each
# pick pool is posted publicly as a generated image. Slot order and the chosen map live in the
# status message. The picks image IS the single draft-start ping: a reply that backlinks the
# status message, captioned with @-mentions so every player is notified.

--- CHAT ---
alice: /lobby
bob: /register
carol: /register
ambotorix: <status *Status: waiting*Players (3): alice, bob, carol*>

alice: /start
ambotorix: <status *Status: drafting*Map: {map}*Slot order:*>
# One combined image: a reply to the status, captioned with the player @-mentions
ambotorix: <image *@alice*@bob*@carol*> <backlink>
ambotorix:                        # group stream fully accounted for (just the one image)

# Players who never opened a private chat receive nothing in DM
--- DM (alice) ---
ambotorix:
--- DM (bob) ---
ambotorix:
--- DM (carol) ---
ambotorix:
